# Student Accommodation Portal (Final Year Project)

This project is a role-based web platform where:

1. Students discover accommodation and food services near universities.
2. Property owners register and publish listings.
3. A chatbot helps users with navigation and listing discovery.

Primary goal: give internal and external examiners a complete, easy-to-follow view of how to run and evaluate the system.

## 1. What The System Includes

- Next.js application with App Router (frontend + backend routes in one project)
- PostgreSQL database using Prisma ORM
- Authentication using NextAuth (credentials provider)
- Role-based flow:
   - Student: search and explore accommodation/food listings
   - Property Owner: create and manage listings
- Chatbot module with:
   - Database-backed assistant route for structured listing lookup
   - Optional Ollama/LLaMA route for local LLM text generation

## 2. Tech Stack

- Framework: Next.js 13
- Language: TypeScript
- UI: Tailwind CSS + component library under components/ui
- Database: PostgreSQL
- ORM: Prisma
- Auth: NextAuth
- Optional local LLM runtime: Ollama (model: llama3)

