## 4. End-To-End Flow (Examiner View)

### 4.1 User Entry Flow

1. User opens / (landing page).
2. If already authenticated:
    - STUDENT -> redirected to /student/dashboard
    - PROPERTY_OWNER -> redirected to /owner/dashboard
3. If not authenticated, user can login/register.

### 4.2 Authentication Flow

1. Registration page submits form-data to POST /api/signup.
2. Backend validates, hashes password, creates user in database.
3. Login uses NextAuth credentials provider.
4. Session JWT stores id, userType, and phone.
5. Protected pages verify session and role before rendering.

### 4.3 Student Functional Flow

1. Student opens /student/search.
2. Frontend applies filters and calls:
    - GET /api/listings/accommodation
    - GET /api/listings/food
3. Results return from Prisma queries.
4. Student reviews listing details and owner contact info.

### 4.4 Owner Functional Flow

1. Owner logs in and opens /owner/add-listing.
2. Owner chooses listing type:
    - Accommodation -> POST /api/listings/accommodation
    - Food service -> POST /api/listings/food
3. Backend enforces PROPERTY_OWNER role and stores listing.
4. Owner sees listing in /owner/listings.

### 4.5 Chatbot Flow

There are two routes currently:

1. /api/assistant
    - Parses text into structured filters.
    - Queries Prisma for matching listings.
    - Returns response text + match count.

2. /api/chat
    - Forwards prompt to Ollama at http://localhost:11434/api/generate.
    - Returns LLaMA-generated reply.

Note: If Ollama is not running, chatbot requests to /api/chat will fail with backend error.

## 5. Local Setup (Exact Order)

Run all commands from:

student_accommodation_portal_full_chat_working_llama/app

### 5.1 Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+ recommended
- npm
- PostgreSQL running locally
- Optional: Ollama running locally for /api/chat

### 5.2 Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

If dependency resolution fails:

```bash
npm install --legacy-peer-deps
```

### 5.3 Configure Environment Variables

Create or update .env in app folder:

```env
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://<username>:<password>@localhost:5432/<database_name>"
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="<any-long-random-secret>"
```

### 5.4 Prisma Setup

```bash
npx prisma generate
npx prisma migrate dev
```

### 5.5 Seed Demo Data

```bash
npx prisma db seed
```

This creates universities, sample students, owners, and listings.

### 5.6 Start The App

```bash
npm run dev
```

Open: http://localhost:3000

